narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Spanish 120 is a terrible course. I don't think I learned very much this semester. I was constantly frustrated because there was so much useless busy work assigned. This course is available to learn spanish and fulfill the language requirement. Take it for that reason.
I would recommend this course. You'll learn a lot of new grammar and phrases that would be very helpful in a Spanish-speaking country.
it was a good class overall- not too much work and expands upon basic spanish
You probably don't have a choice.
dont take if you dont have to
Spanish 120 was more fast-paced than 110, and we learned a lot of new grammar rules in a short amount of time. However, with constant studying, the workload was manageable.
This class is for furthering your knowledge of web tenses and vocabulary.
